genresAdvancedInfo.name: oxford choir
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Oxford choir is a type of choral music that is performed by the choirs of Oxford University. It is characterized by its rich, harmonious sound and its use of traditional choral techniques such as polyphony and counterpoint. Oxford choir music often features religious themes and is performed in the grand, ornate chapels of the university.
